      • inversePermutation

        public static int[] inversePermutation(int[] perm)
        Inverses the given permutation and returns the result. For example, if (2,0,1) is passed, then, in fact, it means (0,1,2) -> (1,2,0) and this method changes it to (0,1,2) <- (1,2,0). This means that if, let say, row 0 moved to 1, now, row 1 should return to 0. For more info, look at the method inversePermuteRowsM in CharMatrix class. Note that the rows numbers are zero-based.
        Parameters:
        perm - the list of permutations.
        Returns:
        the result of inverse permutation list
